# 2p_ctf — client side. Stationary observer on the BLUE team.
# Pairs with 2p_ctf.host.shot. The host arms a BLUE flag carry +
# captures; the client should mirror the state transitions via
# NET_MSG_FLAG_STATE and re-render the flag pips accordingly:
#
#   t60   — lobby (CTF ready) HOME / HOME pips
#   t140  — round just started; both flags HOME
#   t215  — host has carried (BLUE flag pip should pulse alpha)
#   t280  — capture fired; BLUE flag back HOME, score 5-0 RED
#   t320  — post-capture stable; both pips solid HOME again
#
# We don't move; the only purpose is to verify the wire round-trip.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/client_ctf
network connect 127.0.0.1:24017
name ClientBlue

contact_sheet sheet cols 4 cell 320 180

at 60  shot t60_lobby
at 140 shot t140_round_start
at 180 shot t180_settled
at 215 shot t215_host_carries_blue
at 280 shot t280_post_capture
at 320 shot t320_settled
at 700 shot t700_round_end
at 760 end
